The system will rely on the following technical specifications for development:

1.	Programming Language:
o	C++ will be used for developing the backend logic of the system, including the handling of user data, exam processing, and result computation. C++ is chosen for its speed, efficiency, and support for data structures necessary to manage large volumes of exam data.

2.	Libraries:
o	The system will utilize standard C++ libraries to handle input/output operations, string manipulation, and data structure management (e.g., arrays, lists, maps). These libraries are essential for tasks such as reading user input, managing question banks, and processing exam results.

3.	Development Tools:
o	C++ Compilers like GCC, Turbo C++, or Visual Studio Code will be used to write and compile the code. These tools provide an integrated environment for development, debugging, and testing the system’s functionalities.
